ave lives seems to jolt Thig's rigidly trained brain from its accustomed groove, leading him to develop new emotions and thought-processes that he had not experienced before. This transformation also triggers Lewis Terry's realization of his love for Ellen and the need to protect her and her family.&#10;&#10;Therefore, the discovery of an alien world in this text is metaphorically related to the author's writer's block as it suggests that experiencing new emotions, facing challenges, and taking action can inspire creativity and help overcome mental barriers that prevent one from expressing themselves through writing or other forms of art.">
